race.comment: SO YOU ARE (6) wasn't too far away in the Group 3 Newcastle Cup last time out and should find this assignment much more to his liking. Is yet to miss a drum in four starts over this staying trip and is sure to be right there when the whips are cracking. CONNECTICUT (7) got the job done at Lismore at the latest effort and will have derived a stack of confidence from that victory. Winning hoop Bayliss sticks in the saddle and should be going very close again. Former Kiwi SPORTING CHANCE (2) has been right there in all five runs since joining our shores and looks to be building up to a well-deserved win. Has to be included. EL JASOR (4) should be able to sit up on speed and will give backers a sight. BARAZIN (1) next in line with the claim.
